The inverse tangent integral:

:formula_13

The polygamma functions for positive integers &quot;n&quot;:

:formula_14

The Clausen function:

:formula_15

==Integral representations==

The Lerch transcendent has an integral representation:
:formula_16
The proof is based on using the integral definition of the Gamma function to write
:formula_17
and then interchanging the sum and integral. The resulting integral representation converges for formula_18 Re(&quot;s&quot;) &gt; 0, and Re(&quot;a&quot;) &gt; 0. This analytically continues formula_19 to &quot;z&quot; outside the unit disk. The integral formula also holds if &quot;z&quot; = 1, Re(&quot;s&quot;) &gt; 1, and Re(&quot;a&quot;) &gt; 0; see Hurwitz zeta function.

A contour integral representation is given by
:formula_20
where &quot;C&quot; is a Hankel contour counterclockwise around the positive real axis, not enclosing any of the points formula_21 (for integer &quot;k&quot;) which are poles of the integrand. The integral assumes Re(&quot;a&quot;) &gt; 0.

