<doc id="1343185" wikidata="Q3357000" url="?curid=1343185" title="Panteones metro station">
<text>Panteones is a station serving Line 2 of the Mexico City Metro. It is located in the Colonia Argentina district of the Miguel Hidalgo borough of the Mexican Federal District. Panteón means &quot;cemetery&quot; in Spanish; the station&#x27;s name and logo come from the nearby graveyards. The station was opened as part of a westward extension of Line 2 on 22 August 1984.

From 23 April to 24 June 2020, the station was temporarily closed due to the COVID-19 pandemic in Mexico.

==Ridership==
==Nearby==
*Panteón Español, a graveyard
*Panteón Sanctorum, a graveyard

